x4freetext: -RESONANCE STRUCTURE OF S-32 + N FROM TRANSMISSION
AND DIFFERENTIAL ELASTIC SCATTERING EXPERIMENTS.
150 MEV ELECTRON LINAC OF CBNM, GEEL.
.PULSED BEAM OF NEUTRONS PRODUCED IN A MERCURY-COOLED
URANIUM TARGET. 4.5 NSEC BURST WIDTH AND
800 HZ REPETITION RATE. A 37 G/CM2 THICK URANIUM
FILTER IN THE UNMODERATED BEAM WAS USED TO REDUCE
THE EFFECT OF THE GAMMA-FLASH IN THE DETECTOR AND
A 0.4 G/CM2 THICK B-10 C4 FILTER USED TO ABSORB
LOW ENERGY NEUTRONS.
.NATURAL SULPHUR WITH A THICKNESS OF 0.1830 ATOMS
PER BARN, CANNED BETWEEN TWO 0.06 MM THICK
ALUMINIUM FOILS AND MOUNTED ON AN AUTOMATIC SAMPLE
CHANGER AT A 100 M FLIGHT PATH STATION. A NEUTRON
MONITOR WAS USED TO NORMALIZE THE SAMPLE-IN AND
SAMPLE-OUT DATA TO THE SAME NEUTRON SOURCE INTENSITY.
TIME-OF-FLIGHT SPECTROMETER WITH TOTAL FLIGHT
PATH OF 387.713 M (UNCERTAINTY OF 0.012 M).
FOR  TRANSMISSION MEASUREMENTS THE NEUTRONS
WERE DETECTED IN A 15.24 BY 15.24 BY 2.54 CM NE 110
PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR. FOUR 1.9 CM DIAMETER
PHOTOMULTIPLIER TUBES WERE MOUNTED SIDE-ON TO THE
SCINTILLATOR.
FOR THE ELASTIC SCATTERING MEASUREMENTS SIX
NE 110 PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR DETECTORS WITH 5.08 CM
DIAMETER AND 2.54 CM THICKNESS WERE PLACED AROUND
SAMPLE AT LAB ANGLES OF 30, 45, 77, 90, 130, AND
150 DEGREES.
.AFTER BACKGROUND SUBTRACTION, THE SCATTERING DATA
WERE CORRECTED FOR SELF SCREENING AND FOR ATTENUATION
OF THE SCATTERED BEAM IN THE SAMPLE AND IN THE
ALUMINIUM WALL OF THE SCATTERING CHAMBER. THE
CORRECTIONS WERE CALCULATED WITH A MONTE CARLO
COMPUTER CODE WRITTEN FOR THE SPECIFIC GEOMETRICAL
CONDITIONS. THE EFFECT OF MULTIPLE SCATTERING IN THE
SAMPLE COULD BE NEGLECTED.
DATA WAS TAKEN FROM THE MAIN REFERENCE.
P.N.
A.P.T. DATA IN SUBWORK 4 REORDERED
.THE TRANSMISSION DATA WERE ANALYSED WITH THE
MULTI LEVEL BREIT-WIGNER FITTING CODE `SIOB`.
.THE SPIN AND PARITY OF THE RESONANCES WERE
DETERMINED FROM A QUALITATIVE COMPARISON OF
THE EXPERIMENTAL ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTION
WITH CALCULATIONS BASED ON THE BLATT-BIEDENHARN
FORMALISM.
.THE REDUCED WIDTHS WERE CALCULATED ASSUMING AN
INTERACTION RADIUS OF 4.7 FM.
.NO DETAILS GIVEN.
DOUBTFUL L AND J
DOUBTFUL J VALUE
DOUBLET RESONANCE
NOT COMPLETELY RESOLVED FROM NEIGHBORS
DATA FROM TABLE 1 OF MAIN REFERENCE.
P.N.
